1
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,166
Neon: OH! THIS IS
THE FOUNDATION I WANTED!

2
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:21,933
AND THIS LIPSTICK,
THIS SPRAY‐ON MANICURE.

3
00:00:21,966 --> 00:00:24,166
OOH, AND THIS WIG IS SO CUTE!

4
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:27,333
Melody: UM, BOSS, WE REALLY
SHOULD GET GOING SOON.

5
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:31,400
Neon: JUST A SECOND!
I WANT THIS CAMISOLE, TOO.

6
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:33,066
( Basho sighs )

7
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:36,266
ALL THIS SHOPPING'S
GONNA BE THE DEATH OF ME.

8
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,333
Melody: I AGREE.

9
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,566
♪

10
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:47,066
( singing in Japanese )

11
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,484
♪

12
00:02:13,184 --> 00:02:16,150
Neon: IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
I SHOULD BUY WHILE WE'RE HERE?

13
00:02:16,184 --> 00:02:18,150
WHAT ABOUT YOU, ELIZA?
YOU WANT ANYTHING?

14
00:02:18,183 --> 00:02:20,417
Eliza: OH, NO.
I'M FINE. THANK YOU.

15
00:02:20,450 --> 00:02:22,284
‐ ( overlapping chatter )
‐ Neon: HUH? HMM.

16
00:02:25,017 --> 00:02:26,917
I'M GOING TO THE RESTROOM.

17
00:02:27,784 --> 00:02:28,917
DON'T WORRY.

18
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:30,917
JUST WATCH MY STUFF, OKAY?

19
00:02:33,084 --> 00:02:34,784
Basho: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

20
00:02:34,784 --> 00:02:36,950
WILL KURAPIKA BE OKAY?

21
00:02:36,984 --> 00:02:38,350
Melody: I CERTAINLY HOPE SO.

22
00:02:38,417 --> 00:02:40,850
MY FLUTE SHOULD HAVE HELPED
ALLEVIATE HIS FATIGUE,

23
00:02:40,917 --> 00:02:41,950
AT LEAST A LITTLE.

24
00:02:41,984 --> 00:02:44,350
Basho: HMM.
THIS ASSASSINATION...

25
00:02:44,417 --> 00:02:46,084
HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT IT?

26
00:02:46,117 --> 00:02:50,284
Nostrade: THE TEN DONS WILL HIRE
PROS TO HANDLE THE TROUPE.

27
00:02:50,317 --> 00:02:51,484
Kurapika: SIR?

28
00:02:51,517 --> 00:02:53,850
Nostrade: AND SO...

29
00:02:53,917 --> 00:02:57,150
I WANT YOU TO JOIN
THE ASSASSIN TEAM.

30
00:02:57,184 --> 00:02:59,917
Melody: JUDGING BY
THE PACE OF HIS HEARTBEAT,

31
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:02,157
HE WASN'T
ALL THAT HAPPY ABOUT IT.

32
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:05,690
I DON'T BELIEVE HE WANTED
TO JOIN THE ASSASSIN TEAM.

33
00:03:05,757 --> 00:03:07,457
Basho: OF COURSE HE DIDN'T.

34
00:03:07,457 --> 00:03:09,257
Melody: BUT AS YOU WELL KNOW,

35
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,290
KURAPIKA IS
EXTREMELY DETERMINED,

36
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:14,357
AND HE IS WILLING
TO SACRIFICE EVERYTHING

37
00:03:14,424 --> 00:03:18,124
IF IT MEANS THAT HE'S ABLE
TO ACHIEVE HIS DESIRED GOAL.

38
00:03:18,124 --> 00:03:20,190
Basho: NOT AN EASY ROAD TO WALK.

39
00:03:20,257 --> 00:03:22,290
I COULDN'T LIVE THAT WAY.

40
00:03:22,324 --> 00:03:24,790
A LIFE WHERE YOU'RE
BASICALLY KILLING YOURSELF,

41
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:25,790
WHAT'S THE POINT?

42
00:03:25,790 --> 00:03:27,157
Eliza: IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

43
00:03:27,190 --> 00:03:28,924
I HOPE SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

44
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:31,624
Basho: ONCE WE FINISH THIS JOB,

45
00:03:31,624 --> 00:03:35,090
I'M CASHING OUT AND
SEEING THE WORLD ON MY BIKE.

46
00:03:35,124 --> 00:03:36,990
Melody: THAT DOES
SOUND DELIGHTFUL.

47
00:03:37,024 --> 00:03:40,190
Basho: NOT ENJOYING LIFE
IS A CRIME.

48
00:03:40,257 --> 00:03:42,290
Melody: THERE ARE
MANY WAYS TO LIVE.

49
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:45,790
NOT EVERYONE HAS THE SAME IDEAS
ABOUT WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

50
00:03:45,824 --> 00:03:48,157
( Eliza gasping )

51
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:49,790
Basho: HMM?

52
00:03:49,790 --> 00:03:50,957
Melody: SOMETHING WRONG?

53
00:03:50,990 --> 00:03:52,957
Eliza: THE BOSS IS GONE!

54
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:54,924
‐ Basho: WAIT. WHAT?!
‐ Melody: HUH?

55
00:03:56,024 --> 00:03:57,524
Neon: DADDY'S A BIG LIAR.

56
00:03:57,590 --> 00:04:00,757
HE WASN'T GOING TO TAKE ME
TO THE AUCTION,

57
00:04:00,790 --> 00:04:02,264
AND HE PROMISED AND EVERYTHING.

58
00:04:02,297 --> 00:04:05,464
FINE, THEN.
I'LL JUST GO BY MYSELF.

59
00:04:05,464 --> 00:04:07,430
♪

60
00:04:14,464 --> 00:04:15,464
( knock on door )

61
00:04:15,464 --> 00:04:16,830
Mafioso: COME IN.

62
00:04:16,864 --> 00:04:19,364
( door opens, closes )

63
00:04:23,164 --> 00:04:27,364
ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX.

64
00:04:28,297 --> 00:04:30,630
IT LOOKS LIKE EVERYONE IS HERE.

65
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:32,264
Mafioso #2: NO. NOT YET.

66
00:04:32,297 --> 00:04:35,263
Mafioso #1: WHAT? I THOUGHT
THE TEAM HAD EIGHT MEMBERS.

67
00:04:35,297 --> 00:04:37,363
Mafioso #2: NOSTRADE
WILL BE SENDING OVER

68
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:38,797
ONE ADDITIONAL PERSON.

69
00:04:38,797 --> 00:04:42,964
Mafioso #1: EH, THAT BROWN‐NOSER
THE FAKE FORTUNETELLING, EH?

70
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:59,264
ALL RIGHT.
WE'VE GOT EVERYONE ALL TOGETHER.

71
00:04:59,297 --> 00:05:03,104
YOUR MISSION IS TO WIPE OUT
THE PHANTOM TROUPE.

72
00:05:03,137 --> 00:05:05,670
WHEN THE AUCTION
KICKS OFF AGAIN TONIGHT,

73
00:05:05,704 --> 00:05:08,037
THEY MAY COME OUT OF HIDING,

74
00:05:08,104 --> 00:05:13,037
AND IF THEY DO, ELIMINATE THEM
ANY WAY YOU SEE FIT.

75
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:16,504
Assassin: SO ALL OF US ARE
GOING AFTER THE SAME TARGET.

76
00:05:16,537 --> 00:05:17,670
WE SHOULD PICK OUT

77
00:05:17,704 --> 00:05:19,970
SOME CODE NAMES
TO USE FOR EACH OTHER.

78
00:05:20,004 --> 00:05:21,504
Assassin #2: LET'S USE COLORS.

79
00:05:21,537 --> 00:05:23,037
YOU CAN JUST CALL ME BLUE.

80
00:05:23,104 --> 00:05:25,104
Red: I'LL BE RED.

81
00:05:25,137 --> 00:05:27,637
Zeno: IT'S LIKE A GAME,
ISN'T IT?

82
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:30,037
Assassin #1: HMM?
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

83
00:05:30,104 --> 00:05:31,970
‐ Silva: SILVA.
‐ Zeno: ZENO.

84
00:05:32,004 --> 00:05:34,270
Assassin #1: ZENO, EH?
WHAT COLOR'S THAT?

85
00:05:34,304 --> 00:05:36,970
Zeno: WE WILL BOTH USE
OUR REAL NAMES.

86
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:38,270
Blue: YOU WILL?

87
00:05:38,304 --> 00:05:41,337
Silva: YOU ARE WELCOME
TO CALL ME BY MY NAME,

88
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:45,270
BUT I WON'T TAKE ORDERS,
AND WE'LL DO THIS OUR OWN WAY.

89
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:47,804
Assassin #3: HOLD ON.
SILVA AND ZENO?

90
00:05:47,804 --> 00:05:49,870
LIKE OF THE ZOLDYCK FAMILY?

91
00:05:49,937 --> 00:05:51,304
( Kurapika gasps )

92
00:05:51,304 --> 00:05:54,304
Zeno: LET ME KNOW
IF YOU WANT SOMEONE KILLED.

93
00:05:54,304 --> 00:05:58,670
YOU GET 30% OFF
FOR BEING IN THE SAME INDUSTRY.

94
00:05:58,704 --> 00:06:01,377
( assassins gasp )

95
00:06:01,444 --> 00:06:04,677
Kurapika:
SO THEY'RE KILLUA'S FAMILY.

96
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:06,977
Assassin #4:
WE COULD USE CODE NAMES,

97
00:06:06,977 --> 00:06:08,477
BUT DOES IT MATTER?

98
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:10,177
Assassin #5: HE HAS A POINT.

99
00:06:10,210 --> 00:06:13,177
THERE'S NO RULE THAT SAYS
WE HAVE TO WORK TOGETHER.

100
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,977
Assassin #1: BUT WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT THE TROUPE HERE.

101
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:17,777
ATTACKING ALONE
WILL BE DANGEROUS.

102
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:18,777
( assassins grunt )

103
00:06:18,810 --> 00:06:20,544
Assassin #4: AND YOU?

104
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:24,177
Kurapika: SLOPPY TEAMWORK WILL
ONLY SERVE TO CAUSE CONFUSION.

105
00:06:24,210 --> 00:06:26,144
I'LL BE FINE BY MYSELF.

106
00:06:26,144 --> 00:06:27,310
( assassin #4 chuckles )

107
00:06:27,344 --> 00:06:29,810
IT'S FIVE TO FOUR.
THERE YOU GO.

108
00:06:29,810 --> 00:06:32,177
Mafioso #2: THE AUCTION
BEGINS AT 9:00.

109
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:34,644
WE'LL ESCORT YOU
TO THE AUCTION HALL.

110
00:06:34,677 --> 00:06:36,844
WAIT HERE UNTIL IT'S TIME.

111
00:06:37,810 --> 00:06:39,544
( door opens )

112
00:06:39,610 --> 00:06:42,044
Mafioso #1: HEY, NOSTRADE.

113
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,977
HOW DO YOU FEEL, MY FRIEND?

114
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,210
Nostrade: NOT TOO BAD.

115
00:06:45,277 --> 00:06:47,144
Mafioso #1: NOT TOO BAD, HUH?

116
00:06:47,177 --> 00:06:49,110
YOU'RE A BIG SHOT NOW,
AREN'T YOU?

117
00:06:49,144 --> 00:06:53,544
NOT LONG AGO, YOU WERE JUST
HEADING UP A SMALL COUNTRY GANG,

118
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:56,477
AND NOW YOU'RE ACTING
LIKE YOU'RE MY EQUAL.

119
00:06:56,477 --> 00:06:59,510
I HEAR THAT YOU'VE BEEN
WRINGING YOUR HANDS SO MUCH,

120
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:02,317
YOUR SKIN'S RUBBED OFF.
YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY?

121
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:05,017
( laughs )

122
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:07,817
Nostrade: JEALOUSY AMONG MEN
IS PATHETIC.

123
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:10,317
Mafioso #1: BASTARD!

124
00:07:12,817 --> 00:07:15,117
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS,
YOU LITTLE PUNK?

125
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:17,784
IF YOU WANT A PIECE OF ME,
GO AHEAD!

126
00:07:17,817 --> 00:07:20,617
Nostrade: KURAPIKA,
THAT'S ENOUGH!

127
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:21,817
( chains jangle )

128
00:07:22,817 --> 00:07:24,117
Mafioso #1:
GET ONE THING STRAIGHT.

129
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:28,117
NO ONE IS IMPRESSED BY YOU.
DO YOU HEAR ME?

130
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:31,850
( car door closes )

131
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:33,484
Nostrade:
MANY RESENT MY SUCCESS,

132
00:07:33,517 --> 00:07:36,784
BECAUSE THEY'RE UNAWARE
OF THEIR OWN INCOMPETENCE,

133
00:07:36,817 --> 00:07:39,850
BUT I PLAN TO CONTINUE
MY RISE TO THE TOP

134
00:07:39,884 --> 00:07:42,350
USING NEON'S FORTUNETELLING.

135
00:07:42,384 --> 00:07:45,350
I'M DEPENDING ON YOU,
TOO, KURAPIKA.

136
00:07:45,384 --> 00:07:48,484
YOU'LL BE REWARDED
GENEROUSLY IN TIME.

137
00:07:48,517 --> 00:07:50,884
Kurapika: YES, SIR.

138
00:07:51,817 --> 00:07:55,117
( whistle blows )

139
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:58,817
Kurapika: ARE THE POLICE
HELPING YOU?

140
00:07:58,817 --> 00:08:00,984
Nostrade: 60% OF THE VOTES

141
00:08:01,017 --> 00:08:03,890
IN THE YORKNEW CITY MAYOR'S
ELECTION WERE BOUGHT,

142
00:08:03,957 --> 00:08:07,790
AND THE POLICE CHIEF
IS THE MAYOR'S LAPDOG.

143
00:08:07,824 --> 00:08:10,657
IMPOSING TRAFFIC RESTRICTIONS
IS SIMPLE.

144
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:12,390
( cell phone rings )

145
00:08:13,824 --> 00:08:15,224
Kurapika: YES? HELLO.

146
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:18,357
Melody: KURAPIKA, BAD NEWS!
THE BOSS RAN AWAY!

147
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:21,224
SHE CHANGED CLOTHES
WHEN SHE WENT TO THE RESTROOM,

148
00:08:21,290 --> 00:08:23,157
SO SHE MUST HAVE PLANNED AHEAD.

149
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:26,324
Kurapika: DON'T WORRY. I THINK
I MIGHT KNOW WHERE SHE WENT.

150
00:08:26,324 --> 00:08:28,890
GO BACK TO THE HOTEL,
AND STAND BY.

151
00:08:29,824 --> 00:08:30,990
Nostrade: WHAT NOW?

152
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:32,990
Kurapika: YOUR DAUGHTER
HAS RUN AWAY.

153
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:34,890
Nostrade: SHE WHAT?!
( coughs )

154
00:08:34,957 --> 00:08:37,357
Kurapika: SHE'LL LIKELY HEAD
TO OUR DESTINATION.

155
00:08:37,390 --> 00:08:39,224
Nostrade: THE AUCTION?

156
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:41,390
( beeping )

157
00:08:41,457 --> 00:08:42,857
( growls )

158
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:45,290
DAMN. SHE TURNED OFF
HER CELL PHONE.

159
00:08:45,324 --> 00:08:48,324
BUT NEON DOESN'T EVEN HAVE
A PASS TO THE AUCTION.

160
00:08:48,357 --> 00:08:51,390
THEY'LL TURN HER AWAY
WHEN SHE REACHES THE CHECKPOINT.

161
00:08:51,457 --> 00:08:53,490
THIS IS LIGHT NOSTRADE.

162
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:56,357
I NEED FOR YOU TO GIVE AN ORDER
TO THE GUARDS AT THE GATE.

163
00:08:56,390 --> 00:09:00,824
IF A GIRL AROUND 17 OR 18
TRIES TO ENTER WITHOUT A PASS,

164
00:09:00,857 --> 00:09:03,564
TAKE HER INTO CUSTODY.
HER DESCRIPTION IS...

165
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,364
( scanner beeps )

166
00:09:05,397 --> 00:09:07,564
Officer: YOU'RE ALL SET. THANKS.

167
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,130
YOU CAN GO AHEAD NOW.

168
00:09:10,664 --> 00:09:11,997
Neon: WHEW!

169
00:09:11,997 --> 00:09:14,497
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW
TO GET THROUGH THAT GATE,

170
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:16,164
SO THANKS A LOT FOR THE HELP.

171
00:09:16,197 --> 00:09:18,997
Man: HAPPY TO BE OF SERVICE.

172
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:23,197
Nostrade: REALLY?!
WHEN WAS THAT?

173
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:25,164
Officer #2:
ABOUT FIVE MINUTES AGO.

174
00:09:25,197 --> 00:09:27,464
HER HAIR AND CLOTHES
WERE A LITTLE DIFFERENT,

175
00:09:27,497 --> 00:09:29,364
BUT IT WAS PROBABLY HER.

176
00:09:29,397 --> 00:09:31,064
Nostrade: AND SHE
DIDN'T HAVE A PASS?

177
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:32,630
Officer #2:
TO BE PERFECTLY HONEST,

178
00:09:32,664 --> 00:09:35,497
IT DIDN'T SEEM TO ME LIKE SHE
EVEN KNEW SHE NEEDED ONE.

179
00:09:35,497 --> 00:09:38,664
SHE MENTIONED SOMETHING
ABOUT WHO HER DADDY WAS,

180
00:09:38,664 --> 00:09:40,297
BUT THEN SHE JUST LEFT.

181
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:43,897
YES, SHE GOT INTO A TAXI ALONE.

182
00:09:43,964 --> 00:09:46,497
RIGHT. YES, SIR.

183
00:09:46,497 --> 00:09:48,897
Shalnark: THAT OUGHT TO DO IT.

184
00:09:48,964 --> 00:09:50,164
( Nostrade groans )

185
00:09:50,197 --> 00:09:52,564
WHERE COULD SHE HAVE GONE?

186
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:54,997
Kurapika: I'LL SEARCH FOR HER.

187
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:59,297
DO YOU HAVE A MAP
OF YORKNEW CITY?

188
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:01,137
Nostrade: EH?

189
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,437
♪

190
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:07,804
Man: I HEAR YOU'RE
A GOOD FORTUNETELLER.

191
00:10:07,837 --> 00:10:09,270
‐ Neon: HUH?
‐ ( man chuckles )

192
00:10:09,304 --> 00:10:11,004
SOMEONE TOLD ME ONCE.

193
00:10:11,070 --> 00:10:13,237
I CAN'T RECALL WHO.

194
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:15,004
Neon: I AM GOOD.

195
00:10:15,070 --> 00:10:17,004
IMPORTANT PEOPLE
ARE ALWAYS COMING TO ME.

196
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:18,670
Man: HOW ACCURATE ARE YOU?

197
00:10:18,737 --> 00:10:20,404
Neon: THEY SAY I'M ALWAYS RIGHT.

198
00:10:20,437 --> 00:10:22,837
( man chuckles )
"THEY"? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

199
00:10:22,904 --> 00:10:24,137
SHOULDN'T
THE FORTUNETELLER KNOW?

200
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:26,604
Neon: MY HAND MOVES ON ITS OWN.

201
00:10:26,637 --> 00:10:28,004
Man: AH. IMPRESSIVE!

202
00:10:28,070 --> 00:10:29,837
WOULD YOU TELL ME MINE?

203
00:10:29,904 --> 00:10:31,770
Neon: OKAY.
JUST WRITE DOWN YOUR NAME,

204
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:33,137
YOUR BIRTH DATE,
AND BLOOD TYPE,

205
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:35,137
AND THEN I'LL TAKE IT
FROM THERE.

206
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:41,770
Man: THINK THIS'LL WORK?

207
00:10:41,804 --> 00:10:43,004
Neon: LET'S SEE.

208
00:10:43,070 --> 00:10:45,670
YOUR NAME'S
REALLY CHROLLO LUCILFER?

209
00:10:45,737 --> 00:10:47,470
WHAT KIND OF NAME IS THAT?

210
00:10:47,504 --> 00:10:50,437
Chrollo: WELL, MY FRIENDS
JUST CALL ME "BOSS."

211
00:10:50,437 --> 00:10:51,804
( Neon laughs ) BOSS?

212
00:10:51,837 --> 00:10:53,304
WOW! THAT'S EVEN WEIRDER!

213
00:10:53,337 --> 00:10:54,304
( Chrollo chuckles )

214
00:10:54,337 --> 00:10:57,837
Neon: OKAY, HERE GOES.

215
00:11:10,344 --> 00:11:12,944
Kurapika: IT APPEARS
YOUR DAUGHTER IS ALREADY

216
00:11:12,944 --> 00:11:15,444
IN THE CEMETERY BUILDING
ON THE AUCTION SITE.

217
00:11:15,444 --> 00:11:17,910
Nostrade: SHE IS?
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

218
00:11:17,944 --> 00:11:20,777
Kurapika: NOT SURE,
BUT WE NEED TO HURRY.

219
00:11:22,644 --> 00:11:25,144
♪

220
00:11:26,777 --> 00:11:28,610
Neon: THERE. ALL DONE.

221
00:11:28,644 --> 00:11:30,444
Chrollo: THEN CAN I READ IT?

222
00:11:30,477 --> 00:11:32,610
Neon: YEAH, SURE!

223
00:11:32,644 --> 00:11:34,477
MY FORTUNES ARE KINDA STRANGE.

224
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:37,444
THEY'RE USUALLY MADE UP
OF FOUR OR FIVE POEMS.

225
00:11:37,444 --> 00:11:40,777
EACH ONE CORRESPONDS
TO A WEEK OF THAT MONTH,

226
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:43,110
SO THE FIRST ONE MIGHT JUST BE

227
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,810
SOME STUFF
THAT HAPPENED ALREADY.

228
00:11:45,844 --> 00:11:47,777
Chrollo: AH.

229
00:11:52,277 --> 00:11:56,077
FOREVER SET,
A PRECIOUS MOON IS LOST.

230
00:11:56,110 --> 00:12:00,444
THE OTHERS MOURN HIM
WITH CEREMONY GRAND...

231
00:12:00,444 --> 00:12:04,684
RISING UP TO HEAVEN
THE MIGHTY MOON OF FROST

232
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:08,450
WITH A MELODY
FROM THE MOURNING BAND.

233
00:12:14,284 --> 00:12:15,250
( Neon gasps )

234
00:12:25,817 --> 00:12:27,750
♪

235
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:32,186
( Neon gasps )

236
00:12:32,186 --> 00:12:34,353
Chrollo: IT'S AMAZING...

237
00:12:34,386 --> 00:12:36,220
AND CORRECT.

238
00:12:37,186 --> 00:12:40,186
ABOUT THIS FIRST POEM...

239
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,186
Neon: DON'T TELL ME,
PLEASE! REALLY.

240
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:44,586
I NEVER LOOK
AT THE FORTUNES I WRITE.

241
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:46,953
‐ Chrollo: WHY NOT?
‐ Neon: I JUST GET THE FEELING

242
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:50,186
THEY'LL BE A LOT MORE ACCURATE
IF I DON'T GET INVOLVED.

243
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:53,386
Chrollo: THEN WOULD YOU MIND
IF I ASKED YOU A QUESTION?

244
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:54,186
Neon: SURE.

245
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:55,720
Chrollo: THIS VERSE,

246
00:12:55,753 --> 00:12:59,020
IT MAKES REFERENCE
TO A REQUIEM FOR THE DEAD.

247
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:02,560
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN AN AFTERLIFE, NEON?

248
00:13:02,593 --> 00:13:04,293
Neon: HMM.

249
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:06,360
I GUESS I DON'T, NOT REALLY.

250
00:13:06,393 --> 00:13:09,693
FORTUNES ARE ONLY WRITTEN
TO HELP THE LIVING,

251
00:13:09,726 --> 00:13:13,360
AND IN THIS CASE,
THAT'S YOU, MISTER CHROLLO.

252
00:13:13,393 --> 00:13:16,093
A REQUIEM DOESN'T HELP
A DEAD PERSON.

253
00:13:16,126 --> 00:13:18,360
IT COMFORTS THOSE
WHO ARE LEFT BEHIND.

254
00:13:18,393 --> 00:13:20,560
THAT'S WHAT I THINK, ANYWAY.

255
00:13:23,293 --> 00:13:25,726
Chrollo: AND YOU'RE
PROBABLY RIGHT.

256
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,193
LET'S GO.

257
00:13:28,193 --> 00:13:30,693
THE AUCTION PREVIEW
IS ABOUT TO START.

258
00:13:32,026 --> 00:13:34,593
Neon: WHAT I SAID,
I HEARD FROM SOMEONE ELSE.

259
00:13:34,626 --> 00:13:35,860
Chrollo: WHAT?

260
00:13:35,893 --> 00:13:39,193
Neon: A FORTUNETELLER ON TV
SAID IT WHEN I WAS LITTLE,

261
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:41,360
YOU KNOW, WHAT I SAID BEFORE

262
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,193
ABOUT HOW
THE PURPOSE OF FORTUNES

263
00:13:43,226 --> 00:13:45,026
IS TO MAKE
LIVING PEOPLE HAPPY.

264
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,360
Chrollo: OH?

265
00:13:46,393 --> 00:13:49,860
Neon: AND SO THE FORTUNETELLER
TRIED REALLY HARD

266
00:13:49,893 --> 00:13:52,126
TO GIVE
NEGATIVE FORTUNES TO PEOPLE.

267
00:13:52,193 --> 00:13:53,593
Chrollo: NEGATIVE?

268
00:13:53,626 --> 00:13:56,760
Neon: YOU SEE, THAT WAY,
PEOPLE WOULD MAKE AN EFFORT

269
00:13:56,793 --> 00:13:59,793
TO IMPROVE THEIR LIVES
AND TO AVOID MISFORTUNE.

270
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,466
BACK THEN, I CAN REMEMBER

271
00:14:01,533 --> 00:14:04,600
BEING REALLY INSPIRED
BY HOW TRUE THAT WAS.

272
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:08,700
THAT'S WHEN I DECIDED
I WOULD BE A FORTUNETELLER.

273
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:18,266
Chrollo: FOREVER SET,
A PRECIOUS MOON IS LOST.

274
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:21,200
THE OTHERS MOURN HIM
WITH CEREMONY GRAND...

275
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:25,366
RISING UP TO HEAVEN
THE MIGHTY MOON OF FROST

276
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:28,866
WITH A MELODY
FROM THE MOURNING BAND.

277
00:14:28,866 --> 00:14:31,566
HARVEST BARREN, WINE SPILLED,

278
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:35,400
LOVERS SLUMBER
BESIDE THE BLOODY SCARLET EYES.

279
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:38,066
THOUGH CUT IN HALF
SHALL BE YOUR NUMBER,

280
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:41,866
'TIS NOT LOST
WHEREIN YOUR ADVANTAGE LIES.

281
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:44,866
AMUSE YOURSELF
WITH THE ENTR'ACTE.

282
00:14:44,866 --> 00:14:47,600
SEEK OUT NEW FRIENDS
ONCE IN A BIND.

283
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:51,033
PERHAPS TO THE EAST,
ONE CAN BE TRACKED.

284
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:54,700
THE ONE MOST NEEDED,
YOU'RE SURE TO FIND.

285
00:14:55,866 --> 00:14:57,366
Neon: A FEW YEARS LATER,

286
00:14:57,366 --> 00:15:00,566
THAT FORTUNETELLER ENDED UP
GETTING ARRESTED FOR FRAUD.

287
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,073
Chrollo: DO YOU MEAN
THE GALACTIC MATRON?

288
00:15:03,106 --> 00:15:04,373
Neon: THAT'S THE ONE.

289
00:15:04,373 --> 00:15:05,606
Chrollo: IF MEMORY SERVES,

290
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,806
SHE DIDN'T BELIEVE
IN THE AFTERLIFE.

291
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:11,973
Neon: SHE DIDN'T, AND THAT'S WHY
I DON'T BELIEVE IN IT EITHER.

292
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,440
( elevator chimes )

293
00:15:13,473 --> 00:15:16,906
Chrollo: PERSONALLY,
I BELIEVE WE HAVE A SOUL.

294
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:17,973
Neon: HUH?

295
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,606
Chrollo: SEE, THAT'S THE REASON

296
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,373
I WANTED TO FULFILL
MY DEAD FRIEND'S WISH.

297
00:15:22,373 --> 00:15:24,106
IT'S WHAT HE WOULD HAVE WANTED.

298
00:15:24,140 --> 00:15:25,306
Neon: WHAT WISH?

299
00:15:27,373 --> 00:15:29,940
Chrollo: TO WREAK HAVOC.

300
00:15:29,973 --> 00:15:32,473
♪

301
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:34,473
( gasps )

302
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:36,706
ARE YOU OKAY?!

303
00:15:36,706 --> 00:15:38,906
CALL A DOCTOR, QUICKLY!

304
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:42,306
Guard: FIRST FLOOR. WE'RE OVER
BY THE NORTH ELEVATOR.

305
00:15:42,373 --> 00:15:44,606
SOMEONE'S SICK.
CALL AN AMBULANCE.

306
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,706
Mafioso #3: WE CAN'T.
THERE'S NO WAY

307
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:48,573
THEY'RE GONNA LET
AN AMBULANCE COME IN HERE,

308
00:15:48,606 --> 00:15:50,973
NOT IF THEY DON'T HAVE
AN AUCTION PASS ON 'EM.

309
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,206
Chrollo: YOU'RE KIDDING ME!

310
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,540
WHAT IF SHE DIES?
WHAT HAPPENS THEN, HUH?!

311
00:15:54,573 --> 00:15:56,873
SHE'S THE DAUGHTER
OF THE NOSTRADE FAMILY BOSS!

312
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:59,540
IF SHE DIES HERE,
IT'S ON YOUR HEAD, UNDERSTAND?

313
00:15:59,573 --> 00:16:01,580
( mafioso #3 scoffs )
YEAH, I HEARD YOU.

314
00:16:01,613 --> 00:16:04,280
SOME OF THE TEN DONS
ARE BIG FANS OF HERS.

315
00:16:04,313 --> 00:16:06,113
WE'RE ON IT. JUST SIT TIGHT.

316
00:16:06,146 --> 00:16:08,046
HEY! CALL FOR AN AMBULANCE!

317
00:16:08,046 --> 00:16:09,146
Mafioso #4: RIGHT!

318
00:16:09,213 --> 00:16:11,080
Assassin #4:
HEY, TELL ME SOMETHING.

319
00:16:11,113 --> 00:16:13,280
CAN YOU REWIND
WHAT'S ON THIS MONITOR?

320
00:16:13,313 --> 00:16:15,246
Mafioso #5: HMM? SURE.

321
00:16:23,146 --> 00:16:25,280
Assassin #4: THE SWIFTEST CHOP.

322
00:16:25,313 --> 00:16:28,046
ANYONE ELSE
WOULD'VE MISSED IT.

323
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,946
I'VE MISSED THIS EXCITEMENT.

324
00:16:30,980 --> 00:16:33,713
( chuckles )
I FOUND MY PREY.

325
00:16:33,746 --> 00:16:37,380
Mafioso #6: MASTER NOSTRADE,
YOUR DAUGHTER IS RESTING

326
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:40,246
IN ROOM 501
UP ON THE FIFTH FLOOR.

327
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:45,980
Nostrade: THERE'S SIMPLY NO WAY

328
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:47,713
SHE COULD HAVE GOTTEN
HER HANDS ON A PASS.

329
00:16:47,746 --> 00:16:50,246
HOW DID SHE GET IN?

330
00:16:52,146 --> 00:16:54,113
Kurapika:
YOUR DAUGHTER'S PICTURE

331
00:16:54,146 --> 00:16:56,080
IS ACCESSIBLE
ON THE HUNTER WEBSITE.

332
00:16:56,113 --> 00:16:57,880
Nostrade: WHAT?!

333
00:16:57,880 --> 00:17:01,286
Kurapika: MOST LIKELY, SOMEONE
LOCATED THIS PICTURE OF HER

334
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:05,220
ON THE WEBSITE, FOUND HER,
AND BROUGHT HER HERE SOON AFTER.

335
00:17:05,253 --> 00:17:06,486
( Nostrade growls )

336
00:17:06,553 --> 00:17:09,220
I'LL FIND THAT SCUM
AND KILL HIM.

337
00:17:09,253 --> 00:17:10,486
Kurapika: CALM DOWN, SIR.

338
00:17:10,553 --> 00:17:13,053
I DON'T THINK
CAPTURING YOUR DAUGHTER

339
00:17:13,053 --> 00:17:14,386
WAS THEIR PRIMARY OBJECTIVE.

340
00:17:14,386 --> 00:17:17,086
IT'S POSSIBLE
THEY USED HER AS A HOSTAGE,

341
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:19,220
IN CASE THEY COULDN'T
GET INTO THE BUILDING.

342
00:17:19,253 --> 00:17:20,553
( Nostrade grunts )

343
00:17:20,553 --> 00:17:22,453
Kurapika: IT'S DANGEROUS HERE,

344
00:17:22,486 --> 00:17:25,486
SO I'VE CALLED MELODY AND BASHO.
THEY'LL BE HERE SOON.

345
00:17:25,553 --> 00:17:28,320
Nostrade: ARE YOU SURE IT'S WISE
TO LEAVE IT TO THEM?

346
00:17:28,386 --> 00:17:30,886
Kurapika: YOU SHOULD STAY
WITH HER, TOO, SIR.

347
00:17:30,886 --> 00:17:32,253
Nostrade: BUT THE AUCTION‐‐

348
00:17:32,286 --> 00:17:34,320
‐ Kurapika: THERE WON'T BE ONE.
‐ Nostrade: HMM?

349
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,586
Kurapika: THIS WILL BE
A BATTLEFIELD.

350
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:40,253
THE AUCTION IS SURE
TO BE CANCELED AGAIN.

351
00:17:44,386 --> 00:17:45,720
♪

352
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:49,720
Assassin #4: A TRAIL OF BLOOD
DRIPPED ON PURPOSE,

353
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:54,653
ENOUGH TO BE DETECTED, SMELLED
BY ONE OF THE SAME BREED.

354
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:59,720
WE ARE THE SAME, HE AND I.

355
00:17:59,753 --> 00:18:04,660
WE'RE PREDATORS,
BOTH ADDICTED TO KILLING.

356
00:18:08,326 --> 00:18:12,060
Chrollo: DON'T WORRY.
I DON'T USE CHEAP TRAPS.

357
00:18:16,726 --> 00:18:18,226
ONE‐ON‐ONE?

358
00:18:19,726 --> 00:18:22,093
Assassin #4: SOUNDS GOOD.

359
00:18:22,126 --> 00:18:25,093
Feitan: I HAVE A MESSAGE.
THE BOSS SAID,

360
00:18:25,126 --> 00:18:27,760
"COME TO THE CEMETERY BUILDING
AND WREAK HAVOC."

361
00:18:27,793 --> 00:18:29,326
( bone cracks )

362
00:18:29,393 --> 00:18:33,093
Phinks: THE CEMETERY BUILDING'S
NOT TOO FAR FROM HERE.

363
00:18:33,126 --> 00:18:35,060
WHERE ARE THE OTHERS?

364
00:18:35,060 --> 00:18:37,093
Feitan: THINKING
THE SAME THING AS US,

365
00:18:37,126 --> 00:18:39,993
CLEANING UP THE TRASH
ON THE WAY TO THE BUILDING.

366
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:41,960
Phinks: OKAY. THEN, LET'S GO.

367
00:18:41,993 --> 00:18:45,993
Feitan: THERE'S MORE. THE BOSS
ADDED AN UNUSUAL RULE THIS TIME.

368
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:48,060
Phinks: OH, YEAH? WHAT?

369
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:50,593
Chrollo: MAKE IT A BIG SHOW.

370
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:54,560
♪

371
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:59,760
( music playing only )

372
00:19:03,966 --> 00:19:06,233
( chorus singing
in foreign language )

373
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:18,066
Chrollo: FOREVER SET,
A PRECIOUS MOON IS LOST.

374
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:21,566
THE OTHERS MOURN HIM
WITH CEREMONY GRAND,

375
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:27,066
RISING UP TO HEAVEN
THE MIGHTY MOON OF FROST

376
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:31,233
WITH A MELODY
FROM THE MOURNING BAND.

377
00:19:33,766 --> 00:19:36,666
HARVEST BARREN, WINE SPILLED,

378
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:40,900
LOVERS SLUMBER
BESIDE THE BLOODY SCARLET EYES.

379
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,766
THOUGH CUT IN HALF YOUR NUMBER,

380
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:46,300
'TIS NOT LOST,
WHEREIN YOUR ADVANTAGE LIES.

381
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:49,900
AMUSE YOURSELF
WITH THE ENTR'ACTE.

382
00:19:49,933 --> 00:19:53,066
SEEK NEW FRIENDS ONCE IN A BIND.

383
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:57,733
PERHAPS TO THE EAST,
ONE CAN BE TRACKED.

384
00:19:57,766 --> 00:20:03,006
THE ONE MOST NEEDED,
YOU'RE SURE TO FIND.

385
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:05,206
( chorus continues singing )

386
00:20:08,073 --> 00:20:09,673
( assassin #4 sputters )

387
00:20:09,673 --> 00:20:12,173
( laughing )

388
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:15,040
WHY, HUH? TELL ME WHY?!

389
00:20:15,073 --> 00:20:17,206
( laughs )

390
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,173
WHY?

391
00:20:20,073 --> 00:20:22,073
WHY AM I ALIVE?

392
00:20:22,106 --> 00:20:23,540
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

393
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,406
Chrollo: THIS IS AN INDOOR FISH,

394
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:32,406
A NEN FISH THAT CAN ONLY LIVE
IN ENCLOSED SPACES,

395
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,873
A CARNIVORE
THAT PREFERS HUMAN FLESH.

396
00:20:35,906 --> 00:20:39,506
YOU DON'T BLEED OR FEEL PAIN
AS YOU'RE EATEN.

397
00:20:39,506 --> 00:20:43,040
YOU CAN'T DIE
UNTIL THE NEN FISH DISAPPEARS.

398
00:20:43,073 --> 00:20:45,040
( assassin #4 laughs )

399
00:20:45,073 --> 00:20:46,606
WON'T DIE?

400
00:20:46,673 --> 00:20:47,573
( laughs )

401
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:03,580
( laughs )

402
00:21:03,613 --> 00:21:04,613
( wind blowing )

403
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,580
( body thuds )

404
00:21:09,246 --> 00:21:10,580
( Chrollo sighs )

405
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,613
( chorus singing
in foreign language )

406
00:21:18,913 --> 00:21:22,046
FOREVER SET,
A PRECIOUS MOON IS LOST.

407
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:25,680
THE OTHERS MOURN HIM
WITH CEREMONY GRAND...

408
00:21:28,013 --> 00:21:31,446
RISING UP TO HEAVEN
THE MIGHTY MOON OF FROST

409
00:21:31,513 --> 00:21:35,513
WITH A MELODY
FROM THE MOURNING BAND.

410
00:21:35,513 --> 00:21:37,213
( chorus continues )

411
00:21:45,346 --> 00:21:49,046
WELL, UVO, CAN YOU HEAR IT?

412
00:21:50,913 --> 00:21:54,013
WE DEDICATE THIS REQUIEM TO YOU.

413
00:21:56,746 --> 00:22:00,180
Narrator: IT WAS THE BEGINNING
OF A STORMY NIGHT THAT,

414
00:22:00,213 --> 00:22:03,020
WHILE FIERCE
AND DRENCHED WITH BLOOD,

415
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:06,186
WAS SOMEHOW OVERWHELMINGLY SAD.

416
00:22:06,220 --> 00:22:08,353
( orchestra and chorus
continue )

417
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,860
Gon: COMING UP, GON...

418
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:18,460
Killua: AND KILLUA'S...

419
00:23:18,526 --> 00:23:19,593
Both: HUNTERPEDIA!

420
00:23:22,475 --> 00:23:24,141
‐ Gon: I'M GON.
‐ Killua: I'M KILLUA.

421
00:23:24,175 --> 00:23:25,608
Both: AND THIS IS
OUR HUNTERPEDIA!

422
00:23:25,641 --> 00:23:27,141
Gon: TODAY
WE'RE INTRODUCING PHINKS,

423
00:23:27,175 --> 00:23:29,341
A TROUPE MEMBER,
AND HE'S ALSO AN ENHANCER.

424
00:23:29,341 --> 00:23:30,541
Killua: HE'S STRONG ENOUGH

425
00:23:30,608 --> 00:23:32,341
TO PUNCH
STRAIGHT THROUGH A HUMAN BODY.

426
00:23:32,341 --> 00:23:34,508
Gon: AND SOMETIMES
HE DRESSES IN EGYPTIAN CLOTHING.

427
00:23:34,541 --> 00:23:36,341
Killua: YOU'RE THINKING
OF "SPHINX."

428
00:23:37,441 --> 00:23:39,341
♪

429
00:23:40,508 --> 00:23:43,341
Gon: NEXT TIME,
"ASSAULT AND IMPACT."

430
00:23:43,341 --> 00:23:45,675
Killua: OH, GON,
WHEREFORE ART THOU, GON?

431
00:23:45,675 --> 00:23:48,175
Gon: KILLUA, I'M GON.
THAT'S WHEREFORE.

432
00:23:48,175 --> 00:23:49,775
Killua: WAIT. THAT'S IT?!

